latestIgtvVideos.title: BTS + MINI GUIDE TO PRODUCTION DAYS 📷
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A little glimpse into my latest shoot which brought me a lot of firsts!! Sharing more deets + a few tips I’ve learned along the way on all things production day!

PREP:
+ Good night’s rest (at least 8 hours)
+ Give yourself ample time beforehand to reduce stress and anxiety
+ Use calming techniques to get your skin plumpy and juicy
+ Facial massage @facegym
+ Rose quartz roller @complexculturebeauty

PACKING:
+ Pack EVERYTHING and more
+ Outfit, props, accessories, makeup, makeup remover wipes, comfy change of shoes & fit
+ Laptop to pull up mood boards, inspo & campaign briefs if you’re working with one
+ Tons of 💦 

ON SET:
+ Studio rental- fdphotostudio.com 
Studio spaces can def be on the more costly side. This was the most inexpensive option we found for the setting we were looking for!
+ Makeup artist & photographer- usually these services are also booked hourly. My biggest advice is to be as transparent as possible with your budget, project goals and overall vision

Makeup artist: @_akslay
Photographer: @madisonlanephoto

Hope this little mini vlog + guide was helpful! As always ya girl is here to share any and every resource I can. Let me know if you guys wanna see more of these 🤍😘

latestIgtvVideos.title: The year that changed my life (very emotional)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I can’t even begin to wrap my head around this past year. Leaving a full time job at the end of May and starting my journey into the entrepreneur world was one of the scariest things I’ve ever done in my life.

Running a business completely by myself. Networking, pitching, landing, hustling, creating, building- it’s all been a web of tasks that have taught me more than I’ve ever learned in any other job I’ve had.

And as I sit here writing this- I am completely just mind blown.

Faith and perseverance.
Trust and hard work.

They’re not just cliches. They’re not just things we tell ourselves to get us through. They’re very real. They’re the things that make the once impossible, possible.

Wearing my heart of my sleeve with this one for anyone that’s ever had a dream ♥️

As a first generation Dominican, there isn’t a day that goes by where I don’t feel lucky to experience a freedom only possible through the bravery of my family who left everything behind to give us a better life. A journey and story many of us share- and one that should always be protected by the country who was built off of the backs of immigrants. Praying for the safety of our brothers & sisters 🙏🏼♥️ I posted resources on my page if someone you know is in need of them. My dm’s are always open too for a shoulder to lean on. Sending us all the biggest, tightest hug.
